foreign artists, musicians, sportsmen etc… the youths of today are not able to research and learn that the celebrities they tend to support from afar at the end of the day do not and can never love them enough to buy a house or gift them a car. The respect, admiration and love has to be mutual.

This is why Paul instinctively went straight to two sources where he could get the information he wanted – the woman he loved and the God who loved mankind with no strings attached. None of them could judge him or even condemn him due to their love for him:

“In your presence there is fullness of joy,”… which in other translations is joy “unmixed with grief.”

He wanted this joy and believed that they would both (God and Ann) give it to him if he gave them access to his struggles.

Those who are oblivious to such teaching find it hard to understand why Paul even bothered. They haven’t been taught what these three simple words mean:τύμπανον θάλλειν.

It simply means to me, a vessel or jug that pours out something. In Paul’s case it was Gratitude, Hope and Worship. He had learnt through experience that God worked in mysterious ways…. He knew that the things God would use to make this gratitude happen wouldn’t be so readily available for a masher to use for his pleasure but rather for His pleasure.
